subSubSection.paragraph:
Etymology. The specific name (
noggerup
) is a noun in apposition taken from the type locality of this species ( 2km SW of Noggerup, Western Australia ).

PME closer to PLE than to ALE. AME and ALE ringed with short, red and white scales dorsally and short, grey scales laterally and ventrally. Long, white setae project downwards from below AME forming triangular shape (
Fig. 29B, E
). Cuticular surface of clypeus black and covered with short, white and tan setae. Chelicerae dark brown and glabrous. Coxae, labium, and endites pale and mostly glabrous. Sternum dark brown with light covering of fine, tan setae (
Fig. 30C
).

Clypeus lightly covered with short, white setae. Chelicerae dark brown and glabrous. Coxae, endites, and labium dark brown, translucent and mostly glabrous. Sternum dark brown with light covering of fine, white setae (
Fig. 32B, C, F
).
